Draw a polygon around the driveable free space. For detailed        instructions:  https://docs.google.com/document/d/e/2PACX-1vTt5wpUu3fr7PRScWvKD96HiQLmatRtqWLPX2IDYZ7yqi8tlMGXI891Q4MQZDXAXgbXX3wW_3APoF1N/pub
Draw a polygon outlining all free space where a robot could drive from its current position (concrete or brick paths, but not grass/rocks)

-Usually 1 polygon per image
-Polygon edges should extend to the edge of the image
-Overhanging obstacles should be projected into the ground


More details and examples here:  https://docs.google.com/document/d/e/2PACX-1vTt5wpUu3fr7PRScWvKD96HiQLmatRtqWLPX2IDYZ7yqi8tlMGXI891Q4MQZDXAXgbXX3wW_3APoF1N/pub

-Polygon edges should extend to the edge of the image
-Overhanging obstacles should be projected into the ground
